The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Medical hostel clash

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Durgapur, April 12: The boys hostels of Bankura Sammiloni Medical College and Hospital have been shut down following clashes between rival students unions.

 Principal Susanta Banerjee today asked the students to vacate the two hostel buildings, which house 250 students. We will open the hostels only after the situation improves, he said.

 Clashes broke out yesterday between supporters of the SFI the CPMs students wing and the apolitical Students Association over control of hostel rooms. Around 16 students were injured. 




